    <text>
        <body>
            <head>159. Letter From President <persName corresp="reccm3OnsdQpGeNR8">Carter</persName>
                to King <persName corresp="rec8m8MetQlvwXVeh">Hassan II</persName> of <placeName
                    corresp="recLpHNCu4qy8XTDl">Morocco</placeName>
                <note n="1" place="foot" type="source" xml:id="d159fn1">Source: Carter Library,
                    National Security Affairs, Staff Material, Middle East, Subject File, Box 69,
                    Morocco: 3–6/78. No classification marking.</note>
            </head>
            <opener>
                <dateline rendition="#right">
                    <placeName>Washington</placeName>, <date calendar="gregorian" when="1978-04-25"
                        >April 25, 1978</date>
                </dateline>
                <salute>Your Majesty:</salute>
            </opener>
            <p>Thank you for the message brought to Washington by Foreign Minister <persName
                    corresp="rec2K6Ac2fS0pyTqL">Boucetta</persName>.<note n="2" place="foot"
                    xml:id="d159fn2">See <ref target="#d156fn2">footnote 2, Document
                    156</ref>.</note> I regret my schedule did not permit a personal <pb facs="0403"
                    n="382" xml:id="pg_382"/> meeting, but the <persName corresp="rechYUJdMMxy4Djaf"
                    >Vice President</persName> and Secretary <persName corresp="recRM4qiy2MVhNDPu"
                    >Vance</persName> have informed me of their discussions with the Minister.<note
                    n="3" place="foot" xml:id="d159fn3">For a summary of <persName
                        corresp="rec2K6Ac2fS0pyTqL">Boucetta</persName>’s meeting with <persName
                        corresp="rechYUJdMMxy4Djaf">Mondale</persName>, see <ref target="#d156"
                        >Document 156</ref>. For a summary of <persName corresp="recRM4qiy2MVhNDPu"
                        >Vance</persName>’s meetings with <persName corresp="rec2K6Ac2fS0pyTqL"
                        >Boucetta</persName> on the <placeName corresp="recGZlEaPYk6Kf3qK">Western
                        Sahara</placeName>, see <ref target="#d223">Documents 223</ref> and <ref
                        target="#d224">224</ref>.</note>
            </p>
            <p>Secretary <persName corresp="recRM4qiy2MVhNDPu">Vance</persName> had the opportunity
                for a thorough exchange of views with Foreign Minister <persName
                    corresp="rec2K6Ac2fS0pyTqL">Boucetta</persName> on a variety of issues of common
                concern. We welcomed this occasion to consult closely and to obtain from the Foreign
                Minister directly your Government’s views on these important matters.</p>
            <p>As you know, our exchanges here included a full discussion of the specific issue of
                my Government’s public statements regarding the Sahara. I trust Your Majesty now
                appreciates the circumstances under which such statements were made and understands
                that, in all our public statements concerning <placeName corresp="recLpHNCu4qy8XTDl"
                    >Morocco</placeName>, we seek to emphasize the excellent character of bilateral
                    <rs type="compound-subject" corresp="recsWOnchx3QJo5qE">relations</rs>,
                appreciation for the cooperation <placeName corresp="recLpHNCu4qy8XTDl"
                    >Morocco</placeName> traditionally has extended the United States, and the great
                admiration in this country for the courage with which you and your advisers have
                defined <placeName corresp="recLpHNCu4qy8XTDl">Morocco</placeName>’s international
                orientation.</p>
            <p>I have been informed of your suggestion for discussions here in Washington next
                month. Unfortunately, my calendar for May is very crowded, as several state visitors
                are already scheduled, and there will be a <gloss target="#t_NATO_1">
                    <orgName corresp="rec9wzMIGHUgT4FsE">NATO</orgName>
                </gloss> summit in Washington at the end of the month. I suggest, however, that
                through our foreign ministers we find a time for a meeting which will be mutually
                convenient. I look forward to the chance to exchange views with you.</p>
            <p>In the meantime, you have my very best personal wishes and you can be assured of the
                lasting bonds of friendship that bind our two countries.</p>
            <p>Respectfully yours,</p>
            <closer>
                <signed>
                    <persName corresp="reccm3OnsdQpGeNR8">
                        <hi rendition="simple_bold">Jimmy Carter</hi>
                    </persName>
                </signed>
            </closer>
        </body>
